HEADWORD: Eristalis
<hw>E*ris"ta*lis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.]</ety>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>A genus of dipterous insects whose young
(called <xex>rat-tailed larv⟦ae⟧</xex>) are remarkable for their long
tapering tail, which spiracles at the tip, and for their ability to live
in very impure and salt waters; -- also called <altname>drone
fly</altname>.</def></p>

